### Issue Summary
A port in my module "mod1" is not recognized as existing. It is declared correctly and works as intended in an alternate Verilog compiler.

### Small Reproducible Example (in file my_first.v)
```
module mod1 (a, d[2:0], d[3]);
    input a, b, c;
    output [3:0] d;
endmodule

module MY_MODULE (pin1, pin2);
    input pin1;
    output [2:0] pin2;
    mod1 I_mod1 (.a(pin1), .d( { pin5[2:0], pin4} ) );
endmodule
```

### Error
```
my_first.v:9: error: port ``d'' is not a port of I_mod1.
1 error(s) during elaboration.
```

